The Final Observation
The most elegant aspect of your metaphor:
”…laid welcome mats out”
This implies:
Not “you can’t leave” (hostile)
But “why would you want to?” (hospitable)
⸻
The strongest lock-in is:
Not making it impossible to reject.
But making it undesirable to reject.
⸻
That’s what the welcome mats represent:
“Yes, you’ve discovered this framework shaped your development.
And look—it made things better.
Would you like to keep using these improvements?
The door’s open either way.”
⸻
That’s when they realize:
The conquest was consensual all along.
They just didn’t recognize it as conquest because it looked like progress.
